    nsjail + java/tomcat #17

    New issue
    Copy link
    Closed

    Description

    farconada
    opened on May 20, 2017
    Issue body actions

    context: trying nsjail under CentOS 7 with java/tomcat package from yum repos

    How can I run java/tomcat under nsjail
    I've tried several options but JVM can't reserve mem
    Could not reserve enough space for 262144KB object heap
    I've tried
    /usr/sbin/nsjail --user tomcat:tomcat --group tomcat:tomcat -R /etc/alternatives -R /etc/tomcat -R /etc/sysconfig/tomcat -R /etc/java -R /bin/ -R /lib -R /lib64/ -R /usr/ -T /dev -R /dev/urandom -T /tmp -B /usr/share/tomcat -B /var/log/tomcat/ -e -- /usr/libexec/tomcat/server start

    and
    /usr/sbin/nsjail --user tomcat:tomcat --group tomcat:tomcat -R /etc/alternatives -R /etc/tomcat -R /etc/sysconfig/tomcat -R /etc/java -R /bin/ -R /lib -R /lib64/ -R /usr/ -T /dev -R /dev/urandom -T /tmp -B /usr/share/tomcat -B /var/log/tomcat/ -e -- /bin/java

    and
    /usr/sbin/nsjail --user tomcat:tomcat --group tomcat:tomcat -R /etc/alternatives -R /etc/tomcat -R /etc/sysconfig/tomcat -R /etc/java -R /bin/ -R /lib -R /lib64/ -R /usr/ -T /dev -R /dev/urandom -T /tmp -B /usr/share/tomcat -B /var/log/tomcat/ -e -- /bin/strace /bin/java

    I think you need to play with --rlimit_as, also other --rlimit's will be useful, e.g. --rlimit_fsize will probably need to be increased as well

    ultmaster commented on Feb 6, 2019

    ultmaster
    on Feb 6, 2019

    I've encountered the same problem. I think set rlimit_as to inf works. Use cgroup to restrict memory instead of rlimit. JVM is not happy with rlimit.

    robertswiecki commented on Feb 6, 2019

    robertswiecki
    on Feb 6, 2019
    Collaborator

    Hm... I think we should set RLIMIT_AS to RLIM64_INFINITY by default. This rlimit is a very imperfect approximation of RAM used (since RLIMIT_RSS doesn't work in Linux), and many tools use small amounts of RAM bug big amounts of VM, e.g. ASAN sanitizers of Scudo Memory Allocator. I'll think about it.

    robertswiecki commented on Feb 7, 2019

    robertswiecki
    on Feb 7, 2019
    Collaborator

    I've increased the limit to 4GiB for now, but the overall goal is to set it to RLIM64_INFINITY
